12.  Outputs will include written portions of RCI knowledge products and content of website, written 
economic  updates  and  analysis  and  reports,  updated  ARIC  FTA  database,  and  report  on  website 
improvements under the ARIC FTA database. 

4.  Web Administrator and Programmer (18 person-months) 
13.  Under the supervision of ADB staff and the ARIC lead economist, the consultants will  
(i)  design and develop improved navigational tools using state-of-the-art technologies; 
(ii)  build and maintain efficient content management systems to track and manage content; 
(iii)  build interactive interfaces, geographic data mapper and charting components;  
(iv)  develop a multimedia facility to manage image galleries, podcasts, and video feeds; 
(v)  implement a tracking system to track website statistics on user hits and visits;  
(vi)  maintain programs to update the content of the new website, including page design; 
(vii)  check the entire database for errors; and manage the file structure of the entire website; 
(viii)  post daily updates on the development, intranet, and global websites; 
(ix)  prepare technical documentation for the designed website; and 
(x)  conduct usability tests to evaluate and measure the website’s ease of use. 

14.  Outputs will include (i) design and development of websites; (ii) reports on website improvements, 
statistics,  description  of  maintenance,  and  development,  and  other  reports  on  intranet,  and  global 
websites; and (iii) preparation of a user and/or operations manual for ARIC system. 

5.  Multimedia Designer and Developer (18 person-months) 
15.  The consultant will undertake graphic design work for the ARIC website. Under the supervision of 
ADB staff and the ARIC lead economist, the consultant will 
(i)  conceptualize designs and develop front-end templates for the ARIC website; 
(ii)  manage and update static contents for the ARIC website; 
(iii)  provide support on site uploads and editing of all ARIC online and published materials; 
and 
(iv)  conceptualize and implement designs for ARIC and OREI promotional materials. 

16.  Outputs will include design, development, and implementation of (i) websites, (ii) OREI working 
papers, and (iii) ARIC multimedia products. 

  6.  System and Database Developer (18 person-months) 
17.  The consultant will be working on a daily basis at ADB headquarters. He or she will report to the 
ARIC lead economist as well as ADB staff as may be directed. The consultant will  
(i)  improve the content management systems for the macroeconomic indicators database; 
(ii)  assist  in  the  supervision  of  database-related  collaboration  projects  with  other  ADB 
departments and external stakeholders; 
(iii)  design and implement front-end web tools; 
(iv)  revise the database and content management systems for current and new contents; 
(v)  prepare documentation for implemented database and content management systems; 
and 
(vi)  conduct and oversee a usability test for the ARIC website.
